        <font color="#000000">PREPARATION</font></font></b><font color="#000000" face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">:<font size="1"><br>
        <br>
        </font>To prepare Green Leaf Puerh use 1-2 teaspoons of leaf per serving 
        (either in a teapot or in individual cups). Cover with hot water (75-80&deg;C, 
        167-176&deg;F) and let steep 1-5 minutes (depending on how light or dark 
        you want the tea) and serve. Green Leaf Puerh tea may be &quot;topped 
        up&quot; in the cup or resteeped in the pot many times. </font></p>
